"I don't have anything against Greek life itself. However, when I see individual brothers who are the butt of the house's joke, guys whose best friends do not know him well at all and are unkind to him, or interesting girls who are disappointed in the fact that when all the sisters are gathered together the conversations revolve solely around dieting and boys - I see time and time again how Greek life stunts emotional growth. I understand that Greek life for some is an amazing bonding experience, especially for those who have not had strong friendship groups of their gender in high school. But I see so many people who have a lot of complaints about the system and the people in their house but choose to stick to it anyway, convincing themselves that the friendships are worth it. I feel sympathetic toward these students and I feel grateful that I have been able to find meaningful, stable, and warm friendships with people who put their happiness and growth before social institutions."
